 A case of possession of drugs has been opened for investigation.  The suspect will appear in the Athlone Magistrate’s Court, once charged. RELATED - WATCH: Children gunned down in Philippi drive-by shooting  In a separate incident on Wednesday morning at approximately 01h45 Metro Police Officers attached to K9 unit were patrolling in the Manenberg area. Metro Police's Ruth Solomons said that the officers received a shot spotter alert and immediately responded to Sabie road, Johan Court Manenberg.  Two suspects between the ages of 27 and 22 in connection with the shootings, were arrested. The officers confiscated a Norinco Star firearm and both suspects were arrested for possession of an illegal firearm. Both suspects were detained at Manenberg Saps.   argusnews@inl.co.za    Cape Argus 